Package ohos.aafwk.content

Class IntentParams

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.aafwk.content.IntentParams
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sequenceable

    public class IntentParams
extends Object
implements Sequenceable
    Stores extra parameter information passed to an Ability.

    Parameter information in IntentParams is saved in the form of key-value pairs. The keys are of the String type, and the values are saved as objects of the Object type. You can use the setParam(java.lang.String,java.lang.Object) method to set parameters.

    Since:
    1

        public boolean marshalling​(Parcel out)
        Marshals an IntentParams object into a Parcel.

        Key-value pairs in the IntentParams are marshalled separately. If any key-value pair fails to be marshalled, false is returned.
